    <p>
        <pre>
        <h2>UBUNTU USERS!</h2><br>

        As of Ubuntu 10.04, the .bash_profile is <b><u>NOT</u></b> being used.  It doesn't run at startup, so the PATH and CLASSPATH aren't being changed.  You will need to:

        <b>sudo gedit .xprofile</b>

        and add this into the file:

        <b>. ~/.bash_profile</b>

        Now edit the .bash_profile:

        <b>sudo gedit .bash_profile</b>

        The end result of the .bash_profile should look something like this:

        PATH=$HOME/Java/bin:$HOME/bin:$HOME/Java/jre/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games
        CLASSPATH=.:$HOME/MySQLConJava/connector.jar:/home/jacob/Tomcat/lib/servlet-api.jar:/home/jacob/Tomcat/lib/mysql-connector-java-5.1.14-bin.jar
        export PATH
        export CLASSPATH

        Now you will need to log off, and log back on.  The new PATH and CLASSPATH will now be used.
    </pre>
